More about Simris
What are local energy systems?
We’re renewing Simris
The system and the technology
The technology behind
Local Energy Systems - eon.se
Local energy systems enable communities to become self-sufficient with electricity from renewable sources, such as solar cells on roofs or small wind turbines.
by E.ON Energidistribution (elnät)
In the village of Simris in southern Sweden, we have created Sweden’s first local energy system. During a trial period, the village will be completely self-sufficient every fifth week, using locally produced electricity from renewable sources.
Large energy system today, local production tomorrow.


