SOURCE: https://www.eon.se/en_US/legal
The personal data is used for statistics and follow-up as well as for profiling in order to offer you a more personalized experience on the eon.se and in the E.ON app “Mitt E.ON”.
Your personal data will only be handled by us and our group companies, data processors and their subcontractors.
Solar cells
Information request
Profiling is an automatic processing of personal data that means that we assess your needs or properties based on data we have received from you and collected from other sources. Profiling means that we weigh up different personal data and categorize them. Categorization forms different target groups with similar characteristics and needs, simply to be able to target relevant communication to you and improve your customer experience. Automatic processing means that the assessment of your properties and needs is made automated according to certain criteria. No natural person is involved in the categorization of each case. The criteria vary depending on the type of profiling and situation. Profiling aims to understand what information and offers you want from us.
Your personal data will be stored while you are a customer and most data will be deleted no later than 14 months after the end of the customer relationship. In some cases, we have an obligation to keep certain data by law, such as invoice data, otherwise only data is saved where we have a legitimate purpose to process the data.
Personal data may be handed over to other companies within E.ON or to partners. It may be because we have a partnership that requires us to share certain tasks with our partners and it may be to perform the tasks requested by the person concerned. It may also be that we use data processors. When such surrender takes place, we give clear instructions on how the receiving party should process the personal data.
For this survey, the legal basis for our processing is a legitimate interest, we have carefully balanced the privacy impact for you in relation to the benefits that this investigation may ultimately bring to you and us. It is of course also entirely voluntary to participate in the survey.
Your personal data will be stored while you are a contractor to us and will be deleted thirty (30) days after you as a user have become inactive (not done anything in the system for three (3) months) or after  information that you have terminated your employment.
Erasure
Data Controller: E.ON Energidistribution AB
