Your personal data will be stored while you are doing the work on behalf of us and will be deleted one (1) month after your assignment has ended (in case you have applied for permission), otherwise five (5) years after the application was made by a representative (if the application was made by someone other than yourself).
Your personal data will be stored while you are a customer and most data will be deleted no later than 14 months after the end of the customer relationship. In some cases, we are obliged by law to retain certain data such as invoice data, otherwise only data is saved where we have a legitimate purpose to process the data.
In order to investigate possible crimes afterwards, E.ON has legal requirements to save recorded data for a certain period of time, depending on the object being monitored. Recorded material is stored for a maximum of 730 days for control room/operating center or other control space if the object is a protective object and a maximum of 60 days for other spaces and objects. After this time, the material must be deleted. Deletion occurs daily so that the maximum number of days is never exceeded.
