For this processing, it is your consent that is the legal basis for our processing.
In order for the E.ON Home service to be delivered, the connection between the energy solutions connected and the service is stored. Information about the production or use of the energy solution is then retrieved and stored in order to be made available as part of the service. When the service ends, an email is sent with confirmation and information that the deletion is done within 30 days and that the customer until then can change his mind. After 30 days, the account is deleted and the collected information is anonymized.
Profiling is an automatic processing of personal data that means that we assess your needs or characteristics based on data we have received from you and obtained from other sources. Profiling means that we weigh up different personal data and categorize them. Categorization forms different audiences with similar characteristics and needs, simply to be able to direct relevant communication to you and improve your customer experience. An example of the target group is interested in the environment. An automatic treatment means that the assessment of your characteristics and needs is done automated according to certain criteria. No natural person is involved in the categorization of each case. The criteria vary depending on the type of profiling and situation.
More about profiling and how to withdraw your consent can be found under the heading "Energy Solutions" above.
When personal data is provided to us, the person who provides their personal data receives information about:
Profiling aims to understand what information and offers you want to receive from us and how likely you are to change your electricity supplier. Examples of targeted communication are that we send information about solar cells to customers who live in a villa, but not to customers who live in an apartment if these customers did not expressly wish it.
Your personal data will be processed to provide access to systems required to comply with our common agreement.
When it comes to Tell a friend, our legal basis is legitimate interest.
If you do not show an interest in the product after we have contacted you, your personal data will be deleted within 30 days.
If you have previously given consent, you can easily withdraw this. For example, you may have given a special consent to profiling. If you withdraw your consent, we will not process additional personal data or update previously provided information about you if consent is a prerequisite for the processing of the personal data.
We always want to provide you as a customer with relevant information, offers and service and therefore handle personal data for customer relationship enhancing purposes. One example is to target our communication to you through selection, i.e. that you get customized information depending on where you live, what type of agreement you have, how much biogas is consumed, etc.
