The Newsletter Solnytt
Legal basis for processing
E.ON Sverige AB and our subsidiaries in Sweden are the data controllers for the information you provide to us at eon.se or directly to us in some other way. The first part of this page contains a brief and comprehensive description of the legislation and the way we handle personal data. Further down the page you will find links to each special area where there are more detailed descriptions of the processing of personal data.
Your personal data will be used in the E.ON Home service. Your personal data will be processed for the purpose of fulfilling the current agreement regarding E.ON Home and ensuring a future contact through more communication channels such as e-mail, telephone and physical visits. Personal data may also be used for market analysis and statistics by E.ON or one of E.ON's partners. Personal data may also be disclosed to and obtained from partners and authorities.
In order to meet the installation warranty of five (5) years, the product guarantees of up to twelve (12) years depending on the product and the power guarantee on the solar cell panels for twenty-five (25) years, we will save the manufacturer name, product name, serial number and your real estate plant ID for twenty-five (25) years after the installation of the solar cells has been carried out. Plant ID is a code with eighteen (18) digits used to identify your property's electrical installation.
for what purpose the personal data is collected
For our sales, it is agreements and legitimate interest that are the legal basis for our processing. When it comes to customer relationship management, we use a legitimate interest as a legal basis when handling personal data for, for example, marketing, profiling, newsletters, statistics and analysis, development of products and services. Balancing of interests means that we value our interest in implementing it and your interest based on the privacy breach that may entail with this handling.
Categories of personal data we process are customer information, purchase information, technical information, service information, demographic and visit-information on logged-in services. Examples of data in these categories are how long you have been a customer, your consumption, your choice of products, number of facilities, where and how you live, previous purchases, which of our digital services you use, age and data aimed at estimating your household's composition and lifestyle preferences. Examples of situations where profiling is used are marketing, needs-based offers, product and service development, statistics and analysis, newsletters and other information. Personal data may be disclosed to and collected from partners and authorities.
The information we process about you is, for example, name, mobile number, e-mail, birth data, company, client, client's mobile number, city (framework agreement area) signature, KID. The information we have  collected from you or from your employer in the course of the work that you do or will perform for us. If you do not provide the information to us, you will not be able to perform work for us.
When it comes to solar cells, our legal basis is our agreement.
Personal data is normally not provided to companies in non-EU or EEA countries. If this happens, we first ensure that all the legal conditions are met.
In order for us to keep you up to date on your facility and provide you with the best support, we save your name, postal address, phone number and email address for twenty-five (25) years after the installation date. If you move and your property gets a new owner, we will delete your personal data.
