District heating
You can report at any time that you do not want your personal data to be used for profiling. Your cancellation is valid as long as you are an electricity trading customer at E.ON or until you choose to withdraw your deregistration. To unsubscribe, please contact our customer service.
In the case of e-Mobility and charging account, your personal data will be stored while you have an active charging account with us. When you have not used your charging account for two (2) years, you will be deleted in our systems.
Expressions of interest for solar cell
In order for the service to be delivered, the connection between the solar cell plant and the plant number of the property where your solar cell plant is installed is stored. Information on the amount of electricity produced and consumed is obtained from a service at the inverter manufacturer's premises and then stored in order to be made available as part of the service. In order to produce the amounts shown in the investment follow-up, the amount of electricity produced and consumed is used together with information regarding contract tariffs from the customer's electricity contract. The calculated amounts are stored for later display as part of the service. The stored data is deleted when the service is terminated.
Your personal data will be stored while you are an entrepreneur to us and will be deleted ten (10) years after they have been created in the system.
Security
You have the right to request rectification or deletion of any personal data. Similarly, you can request limitation of our processing of your personal data. You also have the right to object to our processing of any personal data.
We always want to provide you as a customer with relevant information, offers and service and therefore handle personal data for customer relationship enhancing purposes. An example is that through selection target our communication to you, that is, you get customized information depending on where you live, what kind of contract you have, how much electricity you consume, etc. In the context of this work, there is so-called profiling.
