Your personal data will be used to be able to carry out the meter change in a smooth manner and if you have given us the opportunity to save your mobile number, we will in the future be able to inform you about interruptions, inspection and troubleshooting of your meter as well as other types of important events.
The purpose of processing your personal data in connection with this survey is to improve your experience as a customer. In this case, the survey is not anonymous as we would like to be able to contact you after the survey is carried out, if necessary.
Your personal data will be stored while you are an entrepreneur to us. The data will be deleted six (6) months after your account becomes inactive. The account will be disabled if all your permissions expire. All permissions associated with your assignment expire if you or your employer announce that you have terminated your employment or assignment. If all permissions are directly attached to a single contract, the permissions will automatically expire at the end of the contract.
In order to perform Individual Measurement or undermeasurement, we may need to store personal data such as address, house number, apartment number, floor, zip code, city, property designation and country. Data such as meter number, measuring point, measuring location and consumption may also need to be saved. To provide a visualization service, we may also need to store information such as username, password and move-in date. Unless otherwise stated below, these will be deleted twelve (12) months after the end of the customer relationship. In the event that the name and social security number need to be stored, these will be deleted twelve (12) months after the meter is installed. In order to account for consumption information in the form of billing data or equivalent, we need to store consumption figures, meter readings and costs. These are deleted thirty-six (36) months after the current measurement. To provide the comfort service SmartKomfort from E.ON Energilösningar AB meter data and temperature sensor ID will be saved for the duration of the contract. In some cases, we are obliged to retain certain data by law, such as invoice data, otherwise only data is stored where we have a legitimate purpose to process the data.
The purpose of processing your personal data is to fulfill our common agreement.
Collection of personal data
Your personal data will be stored while you are a customer of ours and most data will be deleted fourteen (14) months after the customer relationship ends. In some cases, we are obliged to retain certain data by law, such as invoice data, otherwise only data is stored where we have a legitimate purpose to process the data.
Your personal data may be processed in the form of film recordings in the event that you enter one of our facilities. This is done in order to monitor our facilities. Personal data may also be disclosed to and obtained from partners and authorities.
The purpose of processing your personal data is that you should be able to order permissions to your employees or obtain the permissions that you need to be able to do work for us. If we do not receive your information, the work will not be able to be perfor for us.
In order for us to provide you with the best support and service, we store your name, postal address, telephone number and e-mail address during the contract and two (2) years after the end of the service agreement in order to fulfill our obligations.
Cookies settings
The legal basis differs depending on the type of processing of personal data that we carry out and it may be contract, legitimate interest, legal obligation, interests of fundamental importance or consent. The legal basis on which we base each treatment is apparent from the specific information associated with each service and processing.
We have collected the personal data from you in connection to your registration of an user-account and use of the system. If you are not supporting us with your personal data, you are not able use VISEL, eg. use VISEL to register a change (move in / move out) in the electrical installation.
Pre-registration (Föranmälan)
The data we process are, for example, names, E-mail address, certificates, social security number, address, phone number, and actor number (assigned by E.ON), certificate. The information we have collected from you  in the course of the work that you perform or will perform for us. If you do not provide the information to us, you will not be able to do work for us.
For our electricity sales, it is, agreement and legitimate interest that is the legal basis for our treatment. When it comes to customer relationship management, we use a legitimate interest as a legal basis when handling personal data for marketing, profiling, newsletters, statistics and analysis, product and service development. Balancing interests means that we value our interest in implementing it and your interest based on the privacy breach that this may entail with this handling.
The purpose of processing your personal data in connection with surveys is to improve your experience as a customer. In some cases, the survey is not anonymous as we would like to be able to contact you after the survey is carried out if necessary. This is clear in the information. In other cases, the survey is anonymous in that we do not have access to who has answered what in the survey, at the same time that information is stored with the company that provides the tool that we use for surveys.
