Below you will find information about how we handle personal data in the current product or service.
When surrendering, we always take into account the laws and other provisions governing the separation between electricity trading companies and electricity grid companies. This means that personal data cannot always be provided to other E.ON companies even if the person in question had wished to do so.
We do not retain personal data for longer than necessary. When personal data is no longer needed, it is deleted or anonymized. This applies, for example, where a question received by e-mail has been answered or when a contractual relationship has ended and the parties' dealings are finalised. In some cases, data may need to be stored for a longer period of time, for example for accounting purposes.
