Want to register as a supplier? - eon.se
We use the database provider Achilles Utilities NCE (previously Sellihca). There are two types of registrations; simple and full. Information on what type of registration is necessary can be obtained from the relevant Purchaser. If your business with E.ON totals 5 million SEK or more, you need to complete a full registration, and this has an associated administrative fee which is paid to Achilles. If you want to participate in tenders that fall under PPA, you must complete a full registration regardless of the amount of the deal. With a full registration, companies within the Nordic energy market have access to your information.
1-5 categories: 5 000 SEK
6-15 categories: 6 400 SEK
Other tenders (not falling under the PPA)
Register as new supplier
1-3 categories: 2 000 SEK *
16-25 categories: 7 800 SEK
For tenders falling under the PPA (Public Procurement Act)
*Minimum level of registration only for suppliers with a turnover below 1.1 million EUR.
For tenders not governed by the PPA, registration and approval of new suppliers is handled through the SynerTrade platform. New registrations are always initiated by E.ON’s procurement department, by sending an electronic invitation to the supplier.
Our requirements
On registering, you as the supplier must meet certain E.ON specific requirements such as CS (Corporate Sustainability), ethics and morality, environmental and work environment requirements and confidentiality. You can read more about these in the menu on the left.
Log in to change your details
The amount of the fee depends on how many product and service categories that you wish to register. Contract length determines how long you must be registered with Achilles. As long as there is a valid contract you must be registered with Achilles and renew your details and pay a new annual fee.
>25 categories: 10 100 SEK


